  "text": "The problem remains to find the exact rate function of A τ in the anomalous regime for arbitrary noise amplitudes. Most analytical methods rely on the normal scaling of large deviations and, as a result, cannot be applied. This includes the quantum mapping, as mentioned, but also the so-called contraction principle [5] . There is a possibility that one can obtain I(a) by finding the exact generating function of A τ via, e.g., a time-dependent Feynman-Kac equation [CITATION_1] in which k is scaled with time. However, if I(a) is non-convex, then even this method will not work, since the Legendre connection between generating functions and rate functions is lost [7] .",
